      "content": "coping doesn't change the fact that he's gone. it just makes the days a little less painful so i can keep doing this, but i don't want to keep doing it. i feel like i'm just stuck in a waiting room for nothing. sometimes i think the most honest thing to do would be to just stop fighting it and let the silence take over for good. like, what's the point of pretending things get better when they clearly won't?",
